HEADWORD: Cyanopathy
<hw>Cy`a*nop"a*thy</hw> <pr>(-n?p"?-th?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>ky`anos</grk> a dark blue substance + <grk>pa`qos</grk>
affection.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A disease in which the body is
colored blue in its surface, arising usually from a malformation of the
heart, which causes an imperfect arterialization of the blood; blue
jaundice.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cyanophyll</ent>⟦br⟧
